headline: Why Kimberly-Clark (KMB) Shares Are Sliding Today
summary: Shares of household products company Kimberly-Clark (NYSE:KMB) fell 2.6% in the afternoon session after the company detailed the financial impact of its strategic transformation at an investor conference, highlighting significant costs tied to recent divestitures.
